	<td class="alt1">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>Root:  putting a new spin on it</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#330066" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Why not get a bit more specific with the root line and add to the games diversity.<br />
<br />
Personally, I don't see any reason &quot;gameplay&quot; wise why a certain root works in any environment.  Does it make sense that a mob that flies is snagged by tendrils from the ground?  Or creatures that are in a water environment?  <br />
<br />
Suggestions:<br />
<br />
Root line:  works only outside or in  dungeons where the enviroment is appropriate, in other words the ground is beneath you and the mob is on the ground.<br />
<br />
Vortex:  works only on flying creatures.. want them spinning around in a spot as well.. =P<br />
<br />
Anchor:  works only on mobs in water.<br />
<br />
We could even go further:<br />
<br />
Astral Chains:  Spectres, ghosts.. spirit type creatures<br />
<br />
Adherance:  for tiny creatures like brownies an such where I find it hard to believe tendrils could really bind them..  this spell would stick them in place.<br />
<br />
How bout a spell or AA like:<br />
<br />
Quicksand:  run the creature to a predetermined spot and walah.. of course there are resists checks.. maybe you could even be rooted, lol.. that would be awesome.  I am demented at times.  So no marker here, caster has to memorize the area.<br />
<br />
Pit:  again, run the creature to the predetermined spot and walah.. catch here of course is u wouldn't be able to target him.. there would have to be a timer, preferrably random hehe say anywhere from 2 seconds to a minute .. lol, just enuff time for people to think they might have time to do something else besides get away...  oh, again creature is untargetable in the pit and I think it's fairly safe to say he should regenerate his hps as well.<br />
<br />
Wouldn't idea's like this provide oppurtunites to show just a tad of skill instead of just making mobs immune.  Make us work imo, even make it superhard but give us a chance.  Snares btw could be adjusted as well.. just imagine something that a druid couldn't snare an someone else could!!</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td class="alt2">
