</div><br />
<br />
The problem with &quot;Pit&quot; is lets say a group is trying to get a named, or some quest mob with a horribly rediculous spawn timer.  Your guild wants it or you and a couple friends with this type of spell wants it.  The group engages, you Pit it ... spell expires, friend Pits it ... you pit .. friend pits .. you pit .. friend pits .. etc etc etc until they get so horribly peeved it becomes unbearable <br />
<br />
OR in PVP you find some guy that you want to be an ass to .. Pit him ... have your friend pit him ... with enough people you can lock a mob indefinitely.<br />
<br />
How is that NOT an annoyance?<br />
<br />
Truth is ... in ANY spell or ability, you have to look at it from ALL angles.  It's not about one person being superior to another or even thinking one is superior than another.  Point blank: If it *CAN* be exploited, it will be.</div>
